Session 2023.name: Tech Hub
Session 2023.description: The Tech Hub Project is a comprehensive platform that aims to foster innovation, collaboration, and technological advancements by bringing together a diverse range of projects and initiatives. The platform organizes these projects into various categories, enabling efficient exploration and engagement within specific domains of interest. Through this categorization, the Tech Hub Project serves as a hub for knowledge sharing, idea exchange, and networking among individuals, teams, and organizations involved in technology-driven endeavors.

Session 2023.name: Virtual Moise using hand gesture and voice commands
Session 2023.description: The virtual mouse using hand gestures and voice commands desktop application is an innovative and intuitive way to interact with your computer without the need for traditional mouse and keyboard inputs. By utilizing advanced computer vision and speech recognition technologies, this application allows users to control the cursor on their desktop screen simply by moving their hand and making specific gestures in front of a camera.

Session 2023.name: Career Dendogram
Session 2023.description: We are proposing a new system to help students guide for career selection.The proposed Online Career Guidance System will make it easy for students to access the information they need. It will guide students through this process and provide access to verified sites that can help them. The system will also allow students to collect all the information they require and store it in a manner that makes it easy to access. Students will also have access to useful student testimonies and articles by counselors.

Session 2023.name: Cnn based lung cancer detection model
Session 2023.description: The system performed effectively on 10,000 lung cancer images, achieving high training accuracy (96.89%) and validation accuracy (93.20%). It successfully classified non-small cell lung cancer subtypes, squamous cell carcinoma and adenocarcinoma, using previously unseen images.

Session 2023.name: Air Canvas
Session 2023.description: Air Canvas is an interactive project that utilizes OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision) library to create a virtual canvas in the air. It enables users to draw and manipulate digital artwork in real-time using hand gestures and motions captured by a camera The project combines computer vision techniques with image processing algorithms to detect and track the user's hand movements. It allows the user to use their hand as a brush or a tool to interact with the virtual canvas
